            <title>[HBASE-1510] allow zookeeper quorum IPs in DNS as an option</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1510</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;instead of configuring IPs in zoo.conf, allow retrieving the IPs from DNS.  This way we don&apos;t have to supply zoo.conf or any hbase-site.xml to clients.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;eg, one quorum might ahve a dns name of &apos;quorum1&apos;, the hbase path, you could specify the cluster in code like:&lt;br/&gt;
HTable table = new HTable(&quot;/quorum1/hbase/table_name&quot;);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and avoid having to distribute hbase-site.xml or zoo.cfg.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
